KANO – Kano State Governor Abdullahi Ganduje is billed to speak on the potentials of Dala Inland Dry Port (DIDP) for the state, the North and Nigeria on which some neighbouring countries of Niger Republic, Cameroon, Tchad and Central Africa, have already indicated interest to patronize. A statement issued by the commissioner for Information, Malam Muhammad Garba indicated that during the summit, Governor Ganduje is expected to make a presentation. He said the governor is billed to speak on the potentials of Dala Inland Dry Port (DIDP) for the state, the North and Nigeria which also some neighbouring countries of Niger Republic, Cameroon, Tchad and Central Africa, have already indicated interest to fully patronize when it takes-off. The statement also indicated that on the sideline of the forum, Ganduje is scheduled to meet with potential investors in the DIDP which is expected to result in the formalization of a bilateral agreement for Nigeria’s economic development.